Male (
Figs. 5–8, 10
). Similar to female but ocelli slightly bigger, postgenal bridge longer than in female; antenna slightly longer than length of body, with 13 flagellomeres, F1 straight, apically slightly swollen, 1.3× as long as F2, placodeal sensilla on F2–F13. Body length 0.8–1.0 mm (n = 10).
